sub_title: Software Master Specialist at Smartmatic | Physicist
summary:
I am a physicist but I work as software developer. I am the kind of person who is always looking for new challenges; I believe that everything can be improved; I'm always looking to add value to the work environment; I'm a team player; and I follow through on what I set out to achieve.

I love to read academic and technical material that helps me to keep up to date. I like to share my knowledge, hold discussions and lectures on computer science, software engineering, and physics.

During the last years I have been working mainly my skills in computer science, software engineering and leadership. 

My interest in software development started very young when my uncle gave me my first computer (an Apple ][ Plus). Since then, I've kept constant interest in many areas in computer science, software engineering and - since I start high school - physics!

When I started college, I decided to study physics as my main profession. During the last years of my undergraduate studies, I specialized in computational physics. My physics degree and my software development skills helped me to get my first job in the area of subsurface investigation and oil exploration applications. Since then, I have focused my profession more in software development than physics, but it's still a topic that I like to talk and keep up to date as much as possible.
